snippet.title: Indoor Playground Family Fun for Kids Part 3 with Spelling | Ball Pits, Inflatables, Slides, Games
snippet.description:
The theme of this video is "to explore." Taika and Saima visit a big indoor playground.  The playground is loaded with exciting tunnels and passageways which allows for a lot of exploration. In the video, you'll see Taika and Saima playing in a ball pit, climbing different play structures, squeezing through tunnels, jumping on trampolines, driving toy cars, and running and exploring everything they could see.

The video is educational; it's a video designed to introduce toddlers to spelling. Although they may not be able to spell the words yet on their own, the video serves to introduce them to the wonderful world of letters and words. The words spelled are explore, slide, ball, car, climb and tunnel.

In the video, you'll see Taika and Saima playing in a ball pit, climbing different play structures, squeezing through tunnels, jumping on trampolines, driving toy cars, and running and exploring everything they could see.

The video is educational; it's a video designed to introduce toddlers to spelling. Although they may not be able to spell the words yet on their own, the video serves to introduce them to the wonderful world of letters and words. The words spelled are explore, slide, ball, car, climb and tunnel.

snippet.title: Fun with the Kids at Scooter's Jungle Indoor Playground in Simi Valley
snippet.description:
Scooter's Jungle in Simi Valley opened in December 2012 and we stopped by for the first time in February 2013 during an "open play" session. There are 3 slides, 4 bounce houses, including 2 with mini zip lines, and a larger bouncer with basketball hoops. a massive climbing play area, two ping pong tables and more. Everyone was having a blast! Great place for private parties (it was a bit crowded the day we went as it was an "open play" session on a federal holiday!

For more information about Scooter's Village, visit http://www.conejovalleyguide.com/kids-activities-blog/scooters-jungle-simi-valley.html or visit their site directly at http://www.scootersjungle.com/simi-valley.php

snippet.title: Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood FULL EPISODE | Daniel Gets Mad / Katerina Gets Mad | PBS KIDS
snippet.description:
"Daniel Gets Mad"
Daniel Tiger and Prince Wednesday are very excited to play at the beach today. But then it rains, and Mom Tiger says they cannot play outside, making them very mad. Mom Tiger helps the boys deal with their mad feelings. Once they are calm, they can think clearly. They have a grr-ific plan to make an INSIDE beach! 

"Katerina Gets Mad"
It's New Instrument Day at Music Man Stan's Music Shop. Everyone is excited, but Katerina Kittycat gets mad when someone else picks the instrument she wants to play. Music Man Stan helps guide Katerina through her mad feelings. He teaches everyone how to dance, stomp and sing their mad feelings away. This episode deals with mad feelings and offers the strategy- When you feel so mad that you want to ROAR...take a deep breath and count to four. 1...2...3...4...

Best Daredevil Day Ever 1155

One of the families favorite things about October is all of the Halloween decorations. Jenny, Adley and Niko Bear found some awesome bats that go perfect for the holiday and decide to hang them on the door. Adley, being the loving little girl that she is, groups them in families and names them after all of us. 

Once the door is all decorated, the find me downstairs so they can show me the great job that they did. After decorations, Adley comes up with a brand new game called statue! the rules are easy, Adley and Niko are statues, Jenny sells them, and I buy them. But they are crazy. The Adley statue moves around when I'm not looking while the Niko Bear statue has a button to make it come a live and run around the room. haha I love pretend play with the kiddos!!

With the new game done, I have to show you guys a new trick that the kiddos and I learned. We can hang from the ceiling in the kitchen!! It's hilarious, though Jenny wishes we didn't use the house like a park toy. We then head to the backyard splash pad to find some rocks for arts and crafts time.

We love doing little DIY creative projects with the kiddos, but these are extra special, because we are going to take these rocks to the construction site of a brand new LDS Temple. These temples are super important to us, so its awesome that we get to put little memories into the foundation. Adley draws pretty flowers, Niko colors his rock so good, and Jenny makes a cute rock for her and baby Navey and I make a rock about our family and how much we love each other. ( Also with a little pirate theme for pirate island lol)

After dropping of the rocks and doing some work at the lake lot, I'm home for the night! I also brought gifts for the whole family. We have A for Adley shirts again!! We have a brand new company making them and they look so good. The colors are bright, the images look great, and we are excited to share them with you guys again!! Prices are still the same, we want them to be easy for you to get. If you bought a shirt before and there were problems with it, we want to help. After unboxing the surprise, it's time to start our bed time routine and end this amazing Best Day Ever!!
